<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Tutamun on 01-11-2000 02:42 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Don't freeze during dialogs. This would be anoying in multiplayer [!] Maybe there should be a panic button like: "Lets talk about this later on, I first have to do something about this monster standing behind me and tapping on my shoulder" You should be able to continue the dialog later on.

Another thought... What happens if you tell the story and take controll of my Char, and a non story related NPC starts to bugger me? Will the world freeze during storytelling to prevent something like this? This could also be a problem for multiplayer... you could tell the story with the Char that is the game server and the others only watch... or you would have to rewrite the story a bit for multiplayer...

Maybe during Dialogs and Storytelling other NPC's near the player should be set to a more passive mode... No. This is also no good idea in multiplayer... One Char could talk to a NPC while the rest of the group kills all the passive monsters...

If you leave out multiplayer in the initial release then you can think about this stuff later on.
****
NPC's stealing from you could be story related. Please don't let too many NPC's in the game steal from my Char.

</TEXTAREA>
